text:
Fifth Avenue at 118th Street, showing part of Mt. Morris Park.

1888.

Fifth Avenue (left), at the N.E. corner of
East 118th Street (foreground), showing rural conditions prevailing on a rocky ridge on the north side of 118th Street. To the left is the Avenue and Mt. Morris Park at 120th Street.
The row of 3-story dwellings at the right are on the south side of 119th Street and extend to Madison Avenue. See View 2 for this thoroughfare.
This photo was verified with the photographers successors (H. N. Tiemann & Co., No. 176 Lexington Avenue) and checked with their records of which this is No. 116.
1891
H. N. Tiemann, Photo
Gift of Urbrock Colloction

23–25 West 118th Street, north side, between Fifth and Lenox Aves. The view shows a synagogue at this site, named Shaarei Zedek.
July 28, 1932.
P L Sperr.
